The paper deals with communication over a noisy feedback channel, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The interactive scheme introduced in the paper involves low-complexity and low-delay communication, which suggests a possible connection to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of lattices and concatenated coding, which are common techniques in control systems (cs.SY) and multimedia processing (cs.MM). Finally, the paper employs an interactive modulo-lattice solution, which could be related to machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
